An [ABC Dragonfly](/Science_Museum_(London)) engine, a relic of an era when aviation was still figuring out if it wanted to fly or merely fall with style, is preserved at the [London Science Museum](/Science_Museum_(London)).
For a more modern perspective, consider the [CFM56-5B series](/CFM_International_CFM56) engine, a rather ubiquitous beast, as seen installed on an [Airberlin](/Airberlin) [Airbus A320 family](/Airbus_A320_family) aircraft. It’s certainly more reliable than some of the early attempts.
And then there's the [Pratt & Whitney Canada PW127G](/Pratt_%26_Whitney_Canada_PW100) engine, diligently installed on a [RAFO](/RAFO) [EADS CASA C-295](/EADS_CASA_C-295), a workhorse for those who prefer their powerplants to be... predictable.

This is an alphabetical list, meticulously compiled, of [aircraft engines](/Aircraft_engine) by their respective manufacturers. A rather extensive collection, wouldn't you agree?

