[Gio. Ansaldo & C.](/Gio._Ansaldo_%26_C.), a major Italian industrial conglomerate, was deeply involved in shipbuilding, armaments, and, notably, aviation. Their engine division produced a range of powerful inline and V-engines, contributing significantly to Italian air power during World War I and the interwar period.

